      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m afraid that it will require this to implement NullCLLogger, like logger() above does. If m.cllogger() returns nil, archiveLogs() would have to run this check with reflect again against the returned nil, IIUC?\n\nIn a previous comment, Robbie and I agreed to change Archive() to a struct to reduce # of params that have to be passed.\n\ne.g.,\n```\ntype struct Archive {\n   m Manifest\n   streamIDHash []byte\n   ...\n}\n```\n\nI\u0027d rather implement the following instead.\n\nfunc NewArchive(...) Archive {\n   a.isCloudLoggerSet \u003d reflect_check\n   a.isLoggerSet \u003d reflect_check\n}\n\nfunc (a *archiveLogs) archiveLogs(....) error {\n  if a.isLoggerSet {\n     ....\n  }\n\n  if a.isCloudLoggerSet {\n     ....\n  }\n}\n\nLet me know if you have better ideas.\n\nIf I had to implement NullCLLogger, I would remove logger() and cllogger() from common/archive. The caller is responsible to set Manifiest.{Logger,CloudLogger} with nil logger, if necessary.",
